{
  "stem": "93.1",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "In addition to that, you're running into the stench of people who have already died and begun to decay.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "In any event, I quickly realized that this was a big medical problem that we had on our hands.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "And while I could not stay very long because, in combat, you just don't have time to stay anywhere, I went out to my jeep and called our medical doctor, Dr.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "[INAUDIBLE], a major who was the regimental surgeon, and told him that we had this medical problem.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "And I briefly described what I had encountered.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "I must say that before I did this, as I walked out, this German chap came up to me and wanted to shake hands with me.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "And I-- at the point, I almost shot him.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "I was so irritated and-- and horrified by what I had seen.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "But what I did do was I indicated with a wave of my hand that those men that were still able-bodied and strong could have this man.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "And I am absolutely certain that I condemned him to death, for which I have absolutely no remorse.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "And I'm sure they tore him limb from limb when I left, but I just turned on my heels went back to my jeep and called the regiment.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "Now, from Kassel, we turned eastward.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "And the first city in which we, again, encountered the victims of the Holocaust was in Gotha.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "And Gotha was a German city where the camp known as Ohrdruf was-- was located somewhere near Gotha.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "I personally did not see Gotha, but our units liberated it.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "And I have some pictures that were given to me by people that were there, which we can look at later.",
      "word_count": 21
    }
  ],
